Dates and Times:

How do you get the current date and time?
  Time.now or Time.new

How do you find just the Year? Month? Hour? Second? Weekday?
  Year: Date.today.strftime("%Y") => "2017"    or Time.now.year
  Month: Date.today.strftime("%B") => "April"    or Time.now.month
  Weekday: Date.today.strftime("%A") => "Saturday" or Time.now.day
  Hour: Time.now.strftime("%H") => "17"     or Time.now.hour
  Hour: Time.now.strftime("%I") => "05"     
 
  Minute: Time.now.strftime("%M")     or Time.now.min
  Second: Time.now.strftime("%S")     or Time.now.sec 
  Time.now.strftime("%p") => gives PM or AM

How do you create a Time specifically for 12/25/2013?
  Time.new(year, month, day, hour, min, sec, time_zone_offset_from_utc)
  Time.new(2018, april, 15, 02, 30, 30)

How do you find how many days have passed between two Time's?

What's the difference between UTC and GMT and Local times?
  UTC and GMT are same, local time is user's time

